This is the Latin-German dictionary, written by Sebastian Humenda. Please see
the file INSTALL for installation instructions.

The dictionary is transformed from a file called words.xml. This is a condensed
format custom-tailored to the lat-deu dictionary. It is far more efficient than
normal TEI and it's included in the dictibution to inspire future authors.
NOTE: if you plan to edit the TEI source directory, you *have to* exclude the
transformation from words.xml → lat-deu.tei out of the Makefile, otherwise your
work will be lost.

VocaLat uses the FreeDict lat-deu 1.0.3 source release. The exact corresponding
source archive is available at:
https://download.freedict.org/dictionaries/lat-deu/1.0.3/freedict-lat-deu-1.0.3.src.tar.xz
